Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Chop the @tomato{1%medium}(chopped into 1cm pieces) into 1cm pieces and pop into a #large bowl{}. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and sweetcorn. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together and set your salsa aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season with salt and pepper. Fry until golden brown on the outside, ~{7-9%minutes}. Stir in the @Cajun spice mix{1%tbsp} and garlic, then cook for ~{1-2%minutes} more. Remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, combine the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} in a #medium bowl{}. Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the dressing and stir well to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything is ready, pop the tortillas (3 per person) on your plates. Top with a handful of the @wild rocket{20%g} and the Cajun chicken - as much as you'd like. Finish with some sweet chilli slaw and a spoonful of the sweetcorn salsa.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in! Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh, cook the recipe in the same way.